### Test Cregis API Integration
### You can use this file with REST Client extension in VS Code or similar tools

@baseUrl = http://localhost:8000/api

### 1. Get Supported Coins
GET {{baseUrl}}/cregis/coins
Content-Type: application/json

###

### 2. Create Payout
POST {{baseUrl}}/cregis/payout
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "currency": "195@195",
  "address": "TXsmKpEuW7qWnXzJLGP9eDLvWPR2GRn1FS",
  "amount": "10.5",
  "third_party_id": "test_payout_001",
  "callback_url": "http://localhost:8000/api/cregis/callback",
  "remark": "Test withdrawal"
}

###

### 3. Query Payout Status
GET {{baseUrl}}/cregis/payout/test_payout_001
Content-Type: application/json

###

### 4. Test Webhook (simulate Cregis callback)
POST {{baseUrl}}/cregis/callback
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "pid": 1382528827416576,
  "third_party_id": "test_payout_001",
  "status": "success",
  "amount": "10.5",
  "currency": "195@195",
  "timestamp": 1687848653294
}

###
